stylometry:
The standard error of the estimate can be related to standard deviation.  It is similar to standard deviation in the sense that there are an equal amount of data points above and below the line of regression.  

But, where standard error of the estimate comes into play is how close the data points are to the line.  The closer the points are to the line, the smaller the standard error of estimate, which makes our business decision much more confident and secure.  The further the points are from the line means the larger the standard error of the estimate, and therefore would mean that we would be less confident in making a business-like decision.
